.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
Represents a sub-section of a larger terrain for LOD or streaming\&. 

Inherits from \fBMeshTerrain\fP and extracts its data from a global heightmap\&. This allows terrain to be split into smaller pieces for performance and culling\&. 
.SH "Constructor & Destructor Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "TerrainChunk::TerrainChunk ()"

.PP
Default constructor\&. Initializes internal state\&. 
.SH "Member Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "void TerrainChunk::GenerateCPUData (const std::vector< float > & globalHeightmap, int startX, int startZ, int chunkSize, int globalWidth, float minHeight, float maxHeight, float textureScale, const std::vector< std::string > & textureFileNames)"

.PP
Generates mesh data for this chunk from a global heightmap source\&. Generate terrain chunk mesh from a portion of a global heightmap\&.

.PP
This function extracts a rectangular region of height values from a larger terrain and constructs vertex/index buffers only for that portion\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIglobalHeightmap\fP The full terrain heightmap shared across all chunks\&. 
.br
\fIstartX\fP The X-coordinate (column) in the global heightmap to start this chunk\&. 
.br
\fIstartZ\fP The Z-coordinate (row) in the global heightmap to start this chunk\&. 
.br
\fIchunkSize\fP The number of vertices in width and depth this chunk should span\&. 
.br
\fIglobalWidth\fP The full width of the global heightmap (used for indexing)\&. 
.br
\fIminHeight\fP Minimum expected height value (used for \fBAABB\fP normalization)\&. 
.br
\fImaxHeight\fP Maximum expected height value\&. 
.br
\fItextureScale\fP UV scaling factor for this chunk's texture coordinates\&. 
.br
\fItextureFileNames\fP A list of texture file paths to use on this chunk\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBVector3f\fP TerrainChunk::GetOrigin () const"

.PP
Returns the world-space origin of this chunk in terrain units\&. Get the world origin of this chunk based on grid location\&.

.PP
Typically used for placing the chunk correctly in the world or computing transforms\&. 
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
\fBVector3f\fP representing bottom-left corner of the chunk\&.

.PP
\fBVector3f\fP representing the chunk's base position in world space\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "void TerrainChunk::SetSharedTextures (const std::vector< \fBTexture\fP * > & textures)"

.PP
Shares preloaded textures across multiple chunks to reduce memory usage\&. Replace current textures with shared texture pointers\&.

.PP
Replaces this chunk's texture list with a reference to shared ones\&. Textures are not copied or loaded again\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fItextures\fP List of preloaded texture pointers\&.
.br
\fItextures\fP Shared terrain texture list (already loaded and uploaded)\&. 
.RE
.PP

